  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Intranasal dexmedetomidine has shown to be an effective sedative when used prior to
      anaesthetic induction as premedication. 1mcg/kg intranasal dexmedetomidine was used in
      previous study and it produced satisfactory sedation in more than 50% of the children at the
      time of anaesthetic induction with no adverse effect. In this study we aim to compare 1mcg/kg
      with 2mcg/kg intranasal dexmedetomidine in children. We expect more children would attain
      satisfactory sedation prior to anaesthetic induction when higher dose is used.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
